methods.evaluateScript:
Evaluates the script and manages liveness of objects that are exported to the user. This method should be called
 from the serial executor as it manipulates static state.

*Overload 1*  
  :param script: (java.lang.String) - the code to execute
  :param scriptName: (java.lang.String) - an optional script name, which may be ignored by the implementation, or used improve error
          messages or for other internal purposes
  :return: (io.deephaven.db.util.ScriptSession.Changes) the changes made to the exportable objects
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param scriptPath: (java.nio.file.Path) - the path to the script to execute
  :return: (io.deephaven.db.util.ScriptSession.Changes) the changes made to the exportable objects
methods.getVariableProvider:
A VariableProvider instance, for services like autocomplete which may want a limited "just the variables"
 view of our session state.

:return: (io.deephaven.db.util.VariableProvider) a VariableProvider instance backed by the global/binding context of this script session.

text:
This class exists to make all script sessions to be liveness artifacts, and provide a default implementation for
 evaluateScript which handles liveness and diffs in a consistent way.
